{
  "text": "Lung cancer is one of the most common cancers in the world. Gallic acid has a wide range of biological applications and is distributed in a variety of fruits, plants, and foods. A polyhydroxylphenolic compound, gallic acid has antiviral, antibacterial, antimelanogenic, and anticancer activity in a range of cells. Cell cytotoxicity and adhesion studies have shown that superparamagnetic iron oxide nanoparticles are toxic to human dermal fibroblasts, and their internalization results in disruption of the organization of the cytoskeleton in these cells. [CITATION_1] The objective of this work was to synthesize a nanocarrier comprised of ferrite nanoparticles coated with chitosan and gallic acid (FCG) for active drug delivery and specific cell targeting in normal human fibroblasts (3T3) and in cancer cell lines.",
  "citation_candidates": [
